<title>UK: IBJ, London wins Reuter March Forex poll.</title>
<headline>IBJ, London wins Reuter March Forex poll.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>IBJ in London is the winner of the Reuter March foreign exchange poll, beating 33 other banks and financial institutions from across the globe with there forecasts giving an average divergence rate of 0.6148 percent.</p>
<p>In second place came HSBC Global Markets, London with a 0.7678 percent followed by Bank of Montreal in Toronto with 0.8135 percent divergence rates.</p>
<p>The rankings were based on the accuracy of the one month forecasts against the European closing rates on Thursday March 27 of dollar/mark 1.6774, dollar/yen at 123.50 and sterling/dollar at 1.6285.</p>
